Geographical region and time-frame for viagra Country(&region) abbreviations: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2

google.trends <- gtrends(c("viagra"), geo = c("NL", "DE", "ES", "FR"), gprop = "web", time = "2010-01-01 2019-01-01")[[1]]

Plot trend of Viagra from Google in four different countries. If hit is high, it means high google-search-popularity! (Filthy Germans!).

ggplot(google.trends, aes(date, hits, colour = geo)) + 
  geom_point()
